\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b gienensis}  (Degen & Hervier) Heywood,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  65}: 262 (1972) ({\i N. gienensis }Degen & Hervier): Cauline leaves usually shorter than the internodes, not acuminate. Inflorescence with verticillasters less crowded than in ({\b a}). Bracts ovate, cuspidate and slightly toothed, patent, greenish-white, often pink-tinged. Calyx-teeth 2·5-3 × 1 mm, lanceolate. Corolla 9-11 mm, pale blue.{\i  • S. Spain}.
