\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. NEPETA. Most leaves petiolate. Inflorescence spike-like or branched, sometimes leafy below; verticillasters many-flowered. Bracteoles subulate, not rigid, usually much shorter than the calyx. Flowers hermaphrodite. Calyx usually cylindrical or ovoid, often curved; upper teeth usually exceeding the lower. Corolla-tube curved, dilated at the throat. Nutlets smooth or tuberculate.
\par

