\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. N. cataria} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 570 (1753). Stems 40-100 cm, erect, branched, grey-pubescent to tomentose. Leaves 2-8 cm, ovate, acute, cordate at base, crenate or serrate, grey-tomentose beneath; petiole 0·5-4 cm. Inflorescence spike-like, the lower verticillasters distant. Bracts 1·5-3 mm, linear-subulate. Calyx 5-6·5 mm, ovoid; teeth 1·5-2·5 mm, linear-lanceolate, patent.
